    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-12T19:38:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-12T19:38:00-05:00" n="418"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.46E9/10–1251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Ceylon</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-12T19:38:00-05:00"
                            >October 12, 1951—7:38 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>155. Re <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> Senanayake’s recent statement
                    and Ceylon press reports rubber shipment Commie Chi and pt 4 aid. Dept has taken
                    fol line in ans possible questions from press:</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>US opposed shipment rubber Commie Chi in disregard <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                            >UN</gloss> embargo but hopes <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> will
                        stand with other free nations supporting <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                        res.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>US has no objection sale rubber free market which does not contravene
                            <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> embargo. US took every opportunity
                        make above points <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Applicability Kem Amendment Ceylon matter for decision by <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>. Pt 4 only assistance being extended
                        Ceylon. No experts now in Ceylon. Except for few Ceylonese training awards
                        made months ago no aid being extended Ceylon.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
